<TITLE> WC investigation body receives further evidence </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 4 (bdnews24.com)  The War Crimes Fact Finding Committee has submitted documents and evidence to the investigation and prosecution teams set up under the International Crimes (Tribunals) Act 1973. WCFFC convener MA Hasan submitted the documents at the tribunal office, located at the old High Court building, on Sunday. The investigative agency, investigating war crimes committed during 1971, had on Mar 30 formally asked for information from the Liberation War Museum and the WCFFC. Hasan said there are members of the ruling Awami League, the BNP and the Jamaat-e-Islami in the list of war criminals prepared by their organisation. He said that the organisation had prepared a list in April 2008 which identified a total of 1775 war criminals. The list was scrutinised by the National Security Intelligence and Special Branch of police, he said, and was finally sent to the home ministry through the liberation war affairs ministry. The names of BNP leader Salahuddin Quader Chowdhury, former Jamaat chief Golam Azam, current Jamaat chief Motiur Rahman Nizami, Jamaat secretary general Ali Ahsan Mohammad Mojaheed and Jamaat central leader ATM Azharul Islam are included on this list On receiving the evidence Abdul Matin, chief of the investigative agency, said that the evidence would help the agency investigate the crimes. 
